MSTest 3.x+ provides these comparison assertions:

```csharp
Assert.IsGreaterThan(lowerBound, actual);
Assert.IsLessThan(upperBound, actual);
Assert.IsInRange(actual, low, high);
```

They give clear failure messages (e.g., "Expected value to be greater than 0, but was -1") unlike `Assert.IsTrue(x > 0)`.

